OPERATIVES of the Ogun State Police Command have arrested two suspected armed robbers while dispossessing commuters of their belongings on the Long Bridge along Lagos/Ibadan high. According to a statement by the state Police Public Relations (PPRO), DSP Abimbola Oyeyemi, the two suspects, Salam Faruk (18) and Sunday Okechukwu (19), were arrested at about 9:30 p.m on Thursday by policemen on joint patrol operation co-ordinated by the Area Commander of Owode-Egba, ACP Irimiya Asimiya. ALSO READ: Kano Police rescues 4-yr-old from kidnappers who demand N4million ransom The suspects capitalised on the gridlock in the highway to rob commuters before the police busted their activities. Police arrest 39 suspected kidnappers, bandits in Kaduna Police investigate death of 9-yr-old girl, suicide suspected Police recover body of murdered tricycle rider in Anambra,… Police nabbed alleged killer of Keke rider in Anambra Oyeyemi said the policemen, who were on foot patrol of the area, sighted the two suspects, who were armed with dagger knife with which they were forcing commuters to surrender their properties, subsequently went after them before they could jump under the bridge. “On interrogation, the duo confessed to have come from Lagos to the Long Bridge for the purpose of robbing motorists held on gridlock. “The Commissioner of Police, Kenneth Ebrimson, has ordered the immediate transfer of the suspects to Special Anti-robbery Squad (SARS) for discreet investigation. “The commissioner also directed 24 hours surveillance patrol on all the highways across the state so as to checkmate the activities of hoodlums.”  SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
